    public class Game
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is responsible for the game loop. It has status flags that coordinate the game operations.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Game

        public Game()
        Creates a Game set to the first level. The levels are the two predefined levels used in class. showCli is predefined as true.

      • Game

        public Game(int ogreNumber,
            GuardPersonality gp)
        Creates a Game set to the first level. The levels are the two predefined levels used in class except that the guard type/personality can be changed and the number of ogres can too. showCli is predefined as true.
        Parameters:
        ogreNumber - the number of ogres
        gp - the guard personality/type

      • Game

        public Game(char[][] newMapConfig,
            boolean movableChar,
            boolean movableWeapon,
            boolean isLever)
        Creates a Game set to the first and only level. defined on newMapConfig. The level can also have or not movable enemies, movable weapons and a key or a lever (movableChar, movableWeapon and isLever, respectively).
        Parameters:
        newMapConfig - the variable use to create the map
        movableChar - the indicator of enemies movement
        movableWeapon - the indicator of enemies' weapons movement
        isLever - the indicator if newly made level will have a key
